      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "How are these lawmakers avoiding disclosure? One explanation involves loopholes. The Senate ethics panel, for example, only requires disclosure when an outgoing lawmaker actually receives a job offer. Former House Representatives Tom Davis (R-Va.), Jim McCrey (R-La.), and Charles Pickering (R-Miss.) have tried to ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "skirt triggering disclosure requirements",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.citizen.org/wp-content/uploads/report_on_employment_negotiation_8-17.pdf",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " by hiring intermediaries to negotiate future employment on their behalf. Even so, it appears that many lawmakers simply ignore the law.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "A 2017 Public Citizen ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "report",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.citizen.org/wp-content/uploads/report_on_employment_negotiation_8-17.pdf",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " found that out of 408 lawmakers members who retired, resigned, or lost reelection bids between 2007 and 2017, only 16 disclosed negotiations for future employment. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
