            "text": "Politico ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "reported",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.politico.com/story/2016/06/the-lobbying-reform-that-enriched-congress-224849",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " that 47 percent of lawmakers who left Congress between 2008 and 2016 joined the influence industry afterwards. Given the nature of the majority of members‚Äô future employment, the potential for conflicts of interest during negotiations at the end of their terms is alarming.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Congress passed HLOGA to restore public trust in response to a series of damaging corruption scandals. Fifteen years later, it is clear that the law is failing to live up to its promise. This midterm season, as in past election cycles, HLOGA will do little to shield congressional decision-making from the influence of lawmakers‚Äô future employers or even to simply make the public aware of that potential influence.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Without timely public disclosure and recusals, lawmakers may very well be secretly trading their last access to shaping legislation for future monetary compensation.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
